* Iris continues to fire at Prowl as he rampages towards her, her eyes wide 
under the helm. The charges weren't slowing him at all.
She gasped when she saw Prowl about to leap at her, dropping her gun and 
putting her arms infront of her face, only to wait a few seconds when she 
was sure that she'd get hit...and nothing happens. She peeks past her arms, 
seeing Prowl suddenly raise up on his hind legs and screech. Iris winces at 
the sound.

Iron saw Prowl rear back and bellow, gaining ground and increasing the sound 
as much as she could, but too much and she would shatter her own systems. 
She had to keep him from getting at Iris, but then she also saw someone else 
heading for her. (Autofire) < No!>
Her thoughts were shattered and the sound came to an abrupt stop, her mind 
switching to where Autofire was heading.
She hissed at him and charged, spitting a wave of acid at him.
But her circuits had been bumbled around from the sound and the program 
containing her SBM was flictuating, causing her to stumble in her run and 
fall. Her face dug into the ground and she doubled over, wincing.
In seconds the huge shape of the SBM disappeared and all that was left was 
half of her unltrametal mode.
With the torso armor gone, all the was left was the leggings and stability 
plates ( foot armor ). Feeling the sudden chill the armor had prevented her 
from feeling, IR got up to a kneel and discovered that a black tank top 
covered her chest, though her arms and face were bare. Well, now at least 
she wasn't without protection.
Without the helm to keep her hair back it whipped around her face with the 
wind that blew from the south east.
She looked up towards Prowl, not sure of what was going to happen now.*
